      "date": "2014-10-10 13:53:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHonestly, if possible, we should try to avoid using \"startall/stopall\" or similar in our test scripts. Because they are quite time-consuming operations, especially there are many MDTs/OSTs in our test environment. Would you please to measure how long the conf-sanity will run before/after your changes? I am afraid it may cause the Maloo test more slower...",
